00:38:30.240 --> 00:38:32.440
and part of it goes to B.

00:38:32.440 --> 00:38:35.280
And so that's the same you do with A-B testing

00:38:35.280 --> 00:38:40.120
on the production environment.

00:38:40.120 --> 00:38:44.720
And you typically take a certain slice of users,

00:38:44.720 --> 00:38:49.720
let's say, Iowa, and then all the users from Iowa

00:38:50.280 --> 00:38:53.400
get the, all the traffic from Iowa goes through

00:38:53.400 --> 00:38:56.840
a new version of a module of a component,

00:38:56.840 --> 00:38:59.640
in the term of a component.

00:38:59.640 --> 00:39:01.760
And then you see if it works.

00:39:01.760 --> 00:39:02.920
And then if it doesn't work,

00:39:02.920 --> 00:39:05.400
you roll it back as quickly as possible.

00:39:05.400 --> 00:39:09.920
Now it's fail fast and you go back to the old component.

00:39:09.920 --> 00:39:13.440
